# Android magic
First thing I do when I see an .apk in a CTF is to run [apktool](https://ibotpeaches.github.io/Apktool/) and [dex2jar](https://github.com/pxb1988/dex2jar). Second thing is to see what is going on at `AndroidManifest.xml`, reading this file I were able to recognize that there was four activities, and three important ones `PartOneActivity`, `PartTwoActivity`, `PartThreeActivity`. So let's install this apk on the emulator. After installing and opening the app, we face this screen.

![Android MainActivity](./android1.png)

Hitting submit lead us to PartOneActivity, so let's see the source code provided by dex2jar with [jd-gui](http://java-decompiler.github.io/).

## Part one
